</ML_TITLES><ML_AA_NAMES><AA_NAME LG="EN">NHS South West London Clinical Commissioning Group</AA_NAME></ML_AA_NAMES></TRANSLATION_SECTION><FORM_SECTION><F21_2014 CATEGORY="ORIGINAL" FORM="F21" LG="EN"><LEGAL_BASIS VALUE="32014L0024"/><NOTICE TYPE="AWARD_CONTRACT"/><CONTRACTING_BODY><ADDRESS_CONTRACTING_BODY><OFFICIALNAME>NHS South West London Clinical Commissioning Group</OFFICIALNAME><ADDRESS>120 The Broadway</ADDRESS><TOWN>Wimbledon</TOWN><POSTAL_CODE>SW19 1RH</POSTAL_CODE><COUNTRY VALUE="UK"/><E_MAIL>mike.procter@swlondon.nhs.uk</E_MAIL><n2021:NUTS CODE="UKI75"/><URL_GENERAL>www.swlondonccg.nhs.uk</URL_GENERAL></ADDRESS_CONTRACTING_BODY><ADDRESS_CONTRACTING_BODY_ADDITIONAL><OFFICIALNAME>London Borough of Merton</OFFICIALNAME><ADDRESS>Civic Centre, London Road</ADDRESS><TOWN>Morden</TOWN><POSTAL_CODE>SM4 5DX</POSTAL_CODE><COUNTRY VALUE="UK"/><E_MAIL>julia.groom@merton.gov.uk</E_MAIL><n2021:NUTS CODE="UKI75"/><URL_GENERAL>www.merton.gov.uk/</URL_GENERAL></ADDRESS_CONTRACTING_BODY_ADDITIONAL><JOINT_PROCUREMENT_INVOLVED/><CA_TYPE VALUE="BODY_PUBLIC"/><CA_ACTIVITY VALUE="HEALTH"/></CONTRACTING_BODY><OBJECT_CONTRACT ITEM="1"><TITLE><P>Community Services across Merton and Wandsworth Boroughs</P></TITLE><CPV_MAIN><CPV_CODE CODE="85100000"/></CPV_MAIN><TYPE_CONTRACT CTYPE="SERVICES"/><SHORT_DESCR><P>Provision of community services for patients within Merton localities. These service support people to stay well in the community, manage their own health with the right support and avoid stays in hospital. Services work across a wide range of health centres, hospitals, GP surgeries, children’s centres, local council facilities and in community settings – including in people’s homes.</P><P>Provision of community haemoglobinopathy, homeless, refugees and Asylum Seeker team (HRAT) and special school nursing support services for patients within Wandsworth borough.</P></SHORT_DESCR><VAL_TOTAL CURRENCY="GBP">47600000.00</VAL_TOTAL><NO_LOT_DIVISION/><OBJECT_DESCR ITEM="1"><n2021:NUTS CODE="UKI34"/><n2021:NUTS CODE="UKI63"/><MAIN_SITE><P>Boroughs of Merton and Wandsworth.</P></MAIN_SITE><SHORT_DESCR><P>Community services includes provision of the following:</P><P>1) Adults</P><P>(a) unplanned care</P><P>(i) domiciliary therapies;</P><P>(ii) HARI service;</P><P>(iii) falls;</P><P>(iv) in-reach;</P><P>(v) merit urgent;</P><P>(vi) intermediate care (bedded + home + COD);</P><P>(b) planned care;</P><P>(i) Merton case management;</P><P>(ii) continence;</P><P>(iii) dementia;</P><P>(iv) end-of-life care;</P><P>(v) tissue viability;</P><P>(vi) community nursing;</P><P>(c) specialist therapies;</P><P>(i) adult dietetics;</P><P>(ii) adult SLT (incl. sysphagia);</P><P>(iii) diabetes (MDT + Education);</P><P>(iv) neurotherapies (incl. ESD + PD);</P><P>(v) podiatric surgery;</P><P>(vi) podiatry;</P><P>(vii) HIV;</P><P>(viii) cardiology;</P><P>(ix) respiratory;</P><P>2) Children's;</P><P>(a) children's therapies;</P><P>(i) speech and language therapy;</P><P>(ii) physiotherapy;</P><P>(iii) dietetics;</P><P>(iv) OT;</P><P>(v) SN special schools;</P><P>(vi) educational health care plan team;</P><P>(vii) LAC;</P><P>3) Merton other;</P><P>(a) medicines management;</P><P>(b) safeguarding;</P><P>(c) clinical management;</P><P>(d) Marie Curie Night Sitting Service;</P><P>4) Wandsworth Services;</P><P>(a) Community Haemoglobinopathy Service;</P><P>(b) Homeless, Refugees and Asylum Seeker team (HRAT);</P><P>(c) Special School Nursing Support;</P><P>Local Authority Commissioned Services;</P><P>1) 0-19 services (administration);</P><P>2) 0-19 health visiting;</P><P>3) 0-19 school nursing;</P><P>4) Child healthy weight;</P><P>5) Safeguarding;</P><P>6) Clinical management.</P></SHORT_DESCR><NO_EU_PROGR_RELATED/><INFO_ADD><P>The interim contract is for a period of 12 months, with rights reserved to extend for up to a further 12 months (potential 24 months in total). The contract value shown of GBP 47 600 000 is the potential value across 24 months. The 12-month contract value is GBP 23 800 000.</P></INFO_ADD></OBJECT_DESCR></OBJECT_CONTRACT><PROCEDURE><PT_AWARD_CONTRACT_WITHOUT_CALL><D_ACCORDANCE_ARTICLE><D_TECHNICAL/><D_EXTREME_URGENCY/></D_ACCORDANCE_ARTICLE><D_JUSTIFICATION><P>Taking account of the unprecedented impact of Covid-19, the normal commissioning process has been disrupted and it is no longer possible, both in terms of timescales and in terms of service continuity risk, to conduct a competitive procurement for these services ahead of a new contract start date on 1 April 2021.</P><P>NHS South West London CCG, newly formed from April 2020 will need reasonable time following its current response priorities to Covid-19, to assess what future arrangement of community services will best service the patients across the Borough of Merton and also some services provided across the Borough of Wandsworth and then how these new requirements can be put into place. In the interm, the CCG is working collaboratively with key local NHS and local authority system organisations to oversee a development of the community services, including the piloting of new pathways of care within the current level of investment available.</P><P>The incumbent provider is assessed to be the only provider capable of ensuring a continuation of the range and level of service provision currently in place and being delivered sustainably within the finite financial resources available through contract price.</P><P>Observing its obligations under the NHS (Procurement Patient Choice and Competition)(No 2) Regulations 2013, NHS SWL CCG has assessed the appropriateness to award an interim contract directly through a non-competitive process to the incumbent provider(s), recognising an immediate need to ensure continuity of essential patient services whilst a full review takes place to agree the future provision of these services.</P></D_JUSTIFICATION></PT_AWARD_CONTRACT_WITHOUT_CALL><MAIN_FEATURES_AWARD><P>This interim contract is being awarded directly to the incumbent provider.</P></MAIN_FEATURES_AWARD></PROCEDURE><AWARD_CONTRACT ITEM="1"><CONTRACT_NO>1</CONTRACT_NO><TITLE><P>Community Services across Merton and Wandsworth Boroughs</P></TITLE><AWARDED_CONTRACT><DATE_CONCLUSION_CONTRACT>2020-11-27</DATE_CONCLUSION_CONTRACT><TENDERS><NB_TENDERS_RECEIVED>1</NB_TENDERS_RECEIVED></TENDERS><CONTRACTORS><CONTRACTOR><ADDRESS_CONTRACTOR><OFFICIALNAME>Central London Community Healthcare NHS Trust</OFFICIALNAME><ADDRESS>15 Marylebone Road</ADDRESS><TOWN>London</TOWN><POSTAL_CODE>NW1 5JD</POSTAL_CODE><COUNTRY VALUE="UK"/><n2021:NUTS CODE="UKI32"/><URL>www.clch.nhs.uk/</URL></ADDRESS_CONTRACTOR></CONTRACTOR></CONTRACTORS><VALUES><VAL_ESTIMATED_TOTAL CURRENCY="GBP">47600000.00</VAL_ESTIMATED_TOTAL><VAL_TOTAL CURRENCY="GBP">47600000.00</VAL_TOTAL></VALUES><LIKELY_SUBCONTRACTED/><PCT_SUBCONTRACTING>5</PCT_SUBCONTRACTING><INFO_ADD_SUBCONTRACTING><P>Marie Curie Cancer Care</P><P>89 Albert Embankment</P><P>London</P><P>SE1 7TP</P><P>Charity Reg No. 207994</P><P>BUPA Care Homes Limited</P><P>1 Angel Court, London, EC2R 7HJ</P><P>Company Registration Number: 04122364</P></INFO_ADD_SUBCONTRACTING></AWARDED_CONTRACT></AWARD_CONTRACT><COMPLEMENTARY_INFO><ADDRESS_REVIEW_BODY><OFFICIALNAME>High Court</OFFICIALNAME><TOWN>London</TOWN><COUNTRY VALUE="UK"/></ADDRESS_REVIEW_BODY><DATE_DISPATCH_NOTICE>2021-03-25</DATE_DISPATCH_NOTICE></COMPLEMENTARY_INFO></F21_2014></FORM_SECTION></TED_EXPORT>